<div id="content">
<h1>Raúl Díaz García</h1> 

<p>e-mail: rdiazgar (at) uci.edu<br>
   office: 4219 Donald Bren Hall</p>

<p>I was a PhD student at <a href="http://www.uci.edu/">UC Irvine</a>, where I was advised by professor <a href="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~fowlkes/">Charless Fowlkes</a> at the <a href="http://vision.ics.uci.edu/">Computer Vision group.</a></p>

<p>My research focused on improving object detection by finding geometric context cues. In particular, I investigated how structure from motion and multi-view stereo can help in the world of scene understanding.</p>

<p>Since October 2016, I am an intern at HP Inc., working on the Immersive Technology research group.</p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="files/resume.pdf">[resume]</a>   <a target="_blank" href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=O0NVkSwAAAAJ&hl=en">[Google Scholar]</a>   <a target="_blank" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/raúl-díaz-garcía-8720402a">[LinkedIn]</a></p>

<p></p>

